Subject: [experiment] ESM4 native callback actor basis modes

Status: failed experiment, not queued in patches/openmw/series.
Depends-on: 0011-esm4-actor-controller-basis-audit.patch,
0012-esm4-native-callback-basis-audit.patch.
Proof baseline: run/proof-harness-sweeps/20260707-225321.
Proof result: raw mode
run/real-world-screenshots/fallout3-20260707-230543 and
run/real-world-screenshots/fallout_new_vegas-20260707-230612; no-half-turn mode
run/real-world-screenshots/fallout3-20260707-230742 and
run/real-world-screenshots/fallout_new_vegas-20260707-230813; bind mode
run/real-world-screenshots/fallout3-20260707-230948 and
run/real-world-screenshots/fallout_new_vegas-20260707-231022.

The 0012 proof shows the visible FO3/FNV native callback path gets large
applied-versus-raw actor-basis rotation deltas, including 180-degree head/neck
deltas, while face attachment and part telemetry pass. This patch adds a narrow
runtime gate for that exact path without changing default behavior:

OPENMW_ESM4_NATIVE_CALLBACK_ACTOR_BASIS_MODE=current       default
OPENMW_ESM4_NATIVE_CALLBACK_ACTOR_BASIS_MODE=raw           sample raw KF
OPENMW_ESM4_NATIVE_CALLBACK_ACTOR_BASIS_MODE=no-half-turn  raw KF * bind only
OPENMW_ESM4_NATIVE_CALLBACK_ACTOR_BASIS_MODE=bind          bind pose only

The FNV-prefixed legacy env name is also accepted. This is intentionally an
experiment so the proof harness can test modes one at a time and quarantine any
mode that keeps actors inverted or breaks another game.

Result: failed. Raw and no-half-turn kept both FO3 and FNV actors inverted and
FNV crashed after capture. Bind mode exited cleanly and made limbs/weapons a bit
more coherent, but both games still rendered upside-down actors. The next slice
should target actor root/world transform or part attachment basis instead of
native callback keyframe basis modes.

